getARGB(int[], int, int, int, int, int, int) - Method in class ej.microui.io.Image
Obtains ARGB pixel data from the specified region of this image and stores it in the provided array of integers.
Each pixel value is stored in 0xAARRGGBB format, where the high-order byte contains the alpha channel and the remaining bytes contain color components for red, green and blue, respectively.

getFilter(int, int) - Method in class ej.microui.io.GraphicsContext
Gets a filter from the given filter and the given factor.
Given value rgbFilter is interpreted as a 24-bit RGB, where the eight least significant bits matches the blue component, the next eight more significant bits matches the green component and the next eight more significant bits matches the red component.
Each component of this filter is multiplied by the factor and the result is saturate to 0xff.

GraphicsContext uses 24-bit RGB color.
